  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Creative Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>Deliver effective creative work</strong></p><p>Collaborate closely with the Design Director, create designs for your assigned client work and new business pitches. Collaborate and contribute to the thinking, design process and the delivery of client communications. Combine creativity and strategic thinking to proactively challenge a brief, and to interpret business and communications objectives into original and relevant design solutions while working to ensure the integrity, accuracy and quality of work is maintained at all times.</p><p><strong>Be commercially aware</strong></p><p>Manage project resources (time and budgets) to deliver jobs profitably, on time and to the desired quality. Be the champion of our internal work processes. Where required, make an active contribution to new business.</p><p><strong>Support your team</strong></p><p>To work closely with the APAC Creative team, as well as the Account Management and Publishing teams, to understand the creative strategy and delivery framework. Be proactive and helpful, ensuring the smooth running of all projects, exceeding client expectations.</p><p><strong>Your qualifications, experience & skills</strong></p><ul><li>The ideal candidate will have the following profile of skills and experience:</li><li>Diploma or Degree level qualification from a reputable Art/Design college;</li><li>Ideally a minimum of one to three years’ experience in corporate communications, with annual report or sustainability report design experience;</li><li>Expert knowledge of InDesign, Illustrator & Photoshop;</li><li>Good knowledge of the print and production process;</li><li>A passion for digital experience design and digital channels is an advantage;</li><li>Strong interpersonal skill necessary to work with teams and at times, with clients, to build trust and respect;</li><li>Excellent eye for detail, ambitious for the quality of your work, and a constant search for excellence</li></ul><p></p>",
